<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="FO4" checkit-title="Exact First-Order IVPs">
  <statement>
    <p>
        Explain why one of the following ODEs is exact, and why the other is not.
    </p>
      <me>-2 \, t y^{2} + 2 \, y = 12 \, y^{3} {y'} - 4 \, t y {y'} - 6 \, t y</me><me>-3 \, t^{2} + 2 \, t {y'} + 2 \, y = 2 \, t^{2} y {y'} + 2 \, t y^{2}</me>
    <p>
      Then find an implicit solution for the exact ODE
      that satisfies the initial value
        <m>y(-1)=1</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <p>The following ODE is exact.</p>
      <me>-3 \, t^{2} + 2 \, t {y'} + 2 \, y = 2 \, t^{2} y {y'} + 2 \, t y^{2}</me>
    <p>
      Its implicit solution satisfying the initial value is:
    </p>
      <me>-t^{2} y^{2} - t^{3} + 2 \, t y = \left(-2\right)</me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
